ISLAMABAD, Aug 28 (APP): Pakistan on Friday offered its sympathy and condolences to the government and people of Afghanistan at the loss of precious lives and material damage due to heavy rains in Parwan province.
“We stand in solidarity with Afghanistan in this hour of grief and pray for recovery of missing people,” the Foreign Office said in a statement.
